ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: A bizarre but intriguing course about lewin and the role of the listener in analysis. Would definitely recommend!
- rich topic- well-organized course- great professor- adequate time to develop a solid research project

I found the workload to be quite appropriate, though sometimes highly variable from week to week, and would recommend the course toother students because it covers topics that are of very timely concern to the field currently. The course involves some very close reading of central texts and in adequately completing reading assignments multiple readings were helpful.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: I got to think about philosophy!
This course gave me a new perspective on familiar material and spawned a potential dissertation topic. It also familiarized me with a number of key articles in the field.
I believe this course is offered at a timely juncture for some currently work in the field. This course has given me a number of ideas as to possible directions for a dissertation.
